The paper focuses on weakly-supervised learning for semantic segmentation of medical lesions regions, which is a common task in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also proposes a new model that leverages knowledge transfer between different datasets, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of super-pixel spatial prior, which is a common technique in multimedia (cs.MM) and image retrieval (cs.IR).
